description: This header file declares external API function prototypes for the Lpcco TCP component within the ANSC framework. It includes function declarations for creating, removing, enrolling objects, and initializing the component, typically used in a C project related to network service components.

methods.name: AnscCreateLpccoTcp
methods.description: Creates an instance of the Lpcco TCP object with specified container, owner, and reserved contexts.

methods.name: AnscLpccoTcpCreate
methods.description: Creates an instance of the Lpcco TCP object with specified contexts.

methods.name: AnscLpccoTcpRemove
methods.description: Removes the specified Lpcco TCP object, performing cleanup.

methods.name: AnscLpccoTcpEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary objects into the Lpcco TCP instance.
